algorithms.RSSalg.GA

Class Candidate

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.RSSalg.GA.Candidate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Candidate>

    public class Candidate
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Candidate>
    Class representing the candidate for GA optimization in RSSalg. Each candidate is a label agreement threshold and example occurrence threshold pair. The thresholds are used for elimination of "unreliably labeled" examples from the final training set in RSSalg

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Checks whether two candidates result with the same final training set (and accordingly the same final classifier)

        Candidates with different example/label threshold may still have the same set of examples which will be kept in the final training set. For example, consider the statistics:

        • example 1 is labeled by 100% of classifiers and label agreement is 80%
        • example 2 is labeled by 80% of classifiers and label agreement is 70%
        • example 3 is labeled by 50% of classifiers and label agreement is 70%
        Two candidates: candidate1 (example occurrence: 80%, label agreement 70%) and candidate2 (example occurrence: 60%, label agreement 70%) both leave only examples 1 and 2 for the final training set and thus result with the same final classifier.

        This method is convenient to use if classifier training/application on the test set is expensive in order to skip the expensice evaluation of the same classifiers

        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        obj - candidate to compare with
        Returns:
        whether the candidates result with the same final classifier
